How can I use Java to analyze the writing style of two excerpts and compare them? Can I extract the number of adjectives used, the length of sentences, and the use of metaphors or similes? Could you provide an example of how to do this using the given excerpts as input data in the code?
Here is an example Java code that extracts the number of adjectives and sentence length from two given excerpts:
import java.util.regex.Matcher;
import java.util.regex.Pattern;
public class WritingStyleAnalyzer {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String excerpt1 = "The quick brown fox jumped over the lazy dog. It was a bright and sunny day.";
        String excerpt2 = "The lazy dog was jumped over by the quick brown fox. The day was sunny and bright.";
        int adjCount1 = countAdjectives(excerpt1);
        int adjCount2 = countAdjectives(excerpt2);
        int sentLength1 = getAverageSentenceLength(excerpt1);
        int sentLength2 = getAverageSentenceLength(excerpt2);
        System.out.println("Excerpt 1 adjective count: " + adjCount1);
        System.out.println("Excerpt 2 adjective count: " + adjCount2);
        System.out.println("Excerpt 1 average sentence length: " + sentLength1);
        System.out.println("Excerpt 2 average sentence length: " + sentLength2);
    }
    private static int countAdjectives(String text) {
        Pattern pattern = Pattern.compile("\\b([A-Z][a-z]*\\s)?([A-Z][a-z]*\\s)?([A-Z][a-z]*)\\b");
        Matcher matcher = pattern.matcher(text);
        int count = 0;
        while (matcher.find()) {
            count++;
        }
        return count;
    }
    private static int getAverageSentenceLength(String text) {
        String[] sentences = text.split("[.?!]");
        int totalLength = 0;
        for (String sentence : sentences) {
            totalLength += sentence.trim().split("\\s+").length;
        }
        return totalLength / sentences.length;
    }
}
This code extracts the number of adjectives and the average sentence length from two given excerpts. You can modify it to include metaphors or similes by adding additional regular expressions to extract those types of phrases from the text.

