Can you write a MATLAB code to perform a thorough review of an article for grammar, spelling, and overall coherence? The article below discusses the technological innovations that have rapidly transformed our lives after reaching the year 2000.
[Input Data]
After reaching the year 2000, the initial decde of the 21st century brought about a plethora of techonogical innovashuns that have rapidly transformed our lives. Innovations such as smartphones, social media, and cloud computing have made communication and information access more convenient and efficient. In addition, artificial intelligence, virtual reality, and blockchain technology have opened up new possibilities for industries such as healthcare, finance, and entertainment. These innovations have also brought about new challenges such as cybersecurity threats and job displacement. However, the overall impact of these technological advancements on society has been largely positive, shaping the way we live, work, and interact with each other. 
[MATLAB code]
function reviewArticle(article)
    % Remove all punctuation marks
    article = regexprep(article,'[^\w\s]','');

    % Convert all characters to lowercase
    article = lower(article);

    % Split article into individual words
    words = strsplit(article);

    % Remove stop words
    stopWords = ["a", "an", "the", "and", "but", "or", "in", "on", "at", "to", "of", "for", "with", "from", "by"];
    words = setdiff(words, stopWords);

    % Perform spell check
    spellChecked = spell(words);

    % Perform grammar check
    grammarChecked = grammarChecker(spellChecked);

    % Perform coherence check
    coherenceChecked = coherenceChecker(grammarChecked);

    disp(coherenceChecked);
end

