How can I use Java to calculate the nutritional value of various types of fruits, including their size, shape, color, texture, taste, and potential culinary uses? If I have a dataset of these fruits with their corresponding nutritional information, can you provide an example code snippet that demonstrates how to extract and process the necessary data using Java?
Here's an example Java code snippet that demonstrates how to extract and process nutritional information from a fruit dataset:
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;
public class Fruit {
   private String name;
   private double size;
   private String shape;
   private String color;
   private String texture;
   private String taste;
   private List<String> culinaryUses;
   private double calories;
   private double carbohydrates;
   private double protein;
   private double fat;

   public Fruit(String name, double size, String shape, String color, String texture, String taste, List<String> culinaryUses, double calories, double carbohydrates, double protein, double fat) {
      this.name = name;
      this.size = size;
      this.shape = shape;
      this.color = color;
      this.texture = texture;
      this.taste = taste;
      this.culinaryUses = culinaryUses;
      this.calories = calories;
      this.carbohydrates = carbohydrates;
      this.protein = protein;
      this.fat = fat;
   }

   public double getNutritionalValue() {
      return (calories * 0.2) + (carbohydrates * 0.5) + (protein * 0.2) + (fat * 0.1);
   }

   public static void main(String[] args) {
      List<Fruit> fruitList = new ArrayList<>();
      fruitList.add(new Fruit("Apple", 4.5, "Round", "Red", "Crisp", "Sweet", new ArrayList<String>(){{add("Snacks");add("Desserts");}}, 95, 25, 1, 0.3));
      fruitList.add(new Fruit("Banana", 7, "Curved", "Yellow", "Soft", "Sweet", new ArrayList<String>(){{add("Smoothies");add("Baked Goods");}}, 105, 27, 1.3, 0.4));
      fruitList.add(new Fruit("Orange", 5, "Round", "Orange", "Juicy", "Sweet", new ArrayList<String>(){{add("Juices");add("Salads");}}, 62, 15, 1.2, 0.2));
      fruitList.add(new Fruit("Grape", 0.8, "Round", "Green", "Juicy", "Sweet", new ArrayList<String>(){{add("Snacks");add("Salads");}}, 52, 14, 0.6, 0.3));
      fruitList.add(new Fruit("Mango", 10, "Oval", "Yellow", "Juicy", "Sweet", new ArrayList<String>(){{add("Smoothies");add("Salsas");}}, 202, 50, 2.8, 0.4));

      double totalNutritionalValue = 0;
      for(Fruit fruit : fruitList) {
         totalNutritionalValue += fruit.getNutritionalValue();
      }

      System.out.println("The total nutritional value of these fruits is: " + totalNutritionalValue);
   }
}
This code defines a Fruit class with various properties such as name, size, shape, color, texture, taste, culinaryUses, calories, carbohydrates, protein, and fat. It also includes a method to calculate the nutritional value of the fruit based on its calorie, carbohydrate, protein, and fat content.
The main method creates a list of Fruit objects and calculates the total nutritional value of all the fruits in the list. This code can be adapted to handle any fruit dataset and calculate their nutritional values in a similar manner.

